article.headline: Anochili-Killen's 30 lead Marshall over Coastal Carolina 91-74
article.description: — Obinna Anochili-Killen's 30 points led Marshall over Coastal Carolina 91-74 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Anochili-Killen's 30 lead Marshall over Coastal Carolina 91-74
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- — Obinna Anochili-Killen's 30 points led Marshall over Coastal Carolina 91-74 on Saturday night. Anochili-Killen added 10 rebounds for the Thundering Herd (12-12, 7-4 Sun Belt Conference). Kevon Voyles scored 26 points while going 10 of 18 (5 for 11 from 3-point range). Wyatt Fricks had nine points and was 3-of-5 shooting and 2 of 5 from the free-throw line. The Chanticleers (6-16, 3-8) were led in scoring by Jacob Meyer, who finished with 22 points. John Ojiako added 20 points and 13 rebounds for Coastal Carolina. In addition, Kevin Easley Jr. had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
